1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,295
[Ahmad] <i>We will create a public spectacle.</i>

2
00:00:04,379 --> 00:00:07,882
<i>Datu Rahman will surrender himself to me.</i>

3
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:11,094
<i>You will challenge Agent Marcus Reyes</i>

4
00:00:11,177 --> 00:00:14,681
<i>to catch and expose</i>
<i>the people who framed you.</i>

5
00:00:14,764 --> 00:00:16,641
This is the court order you asked for

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,601
for Datu Rahman's custody.

7
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:20,979
- [grunts]
- [glass shattering]

8
00:00:21,062 --> 00:00:24,941
[Manuel] <i>We have to execute</i>
<i>the plan right away.</i>

9
00:00:25,024 --> 00:00:28,361
[Azuelo] <i>Sir, they are the members</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha.</i>

10
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:30,905
<i>They are in charge</i>
<i>of Datu Rahman's security.</i>

11
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:33,450
[Ahmad] <i>Agent Marcus Reyes.</i>

12
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,369
God willing, we get to be with you

13
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,121
in searching for the truth.

14
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:39,748
[in Arabic] And peace be upon you.

15
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:40,874
[screams]

16
00:00:40,957 --> 00:00:46,963
[Manuel] <i>If only you had been</i>
<i>more competent from the start,</i>

17
00:00:47,046 --> 00:00:50,175
<i>I wouldn't have to go</i>
<i>through all this trouble!</i>

18
00:00:50,258 --> 00:00:50,925
- [gunshot]
- [young Lara shrieks]

19
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:52,719
What did you do?!

20
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:58,099
[Lara] So, if capturing Datu Rahman

21
00:00:58,183 --> 00:01:00,060
was such a huge milestone for you,

22
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:01,436
why did you disappear
when the media arrived?

23
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:03,480
I don't need the masses
to sing me praises.

24
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:05,106
You're hiding something, Espina.

25
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:06,816
[Lara] <i>I'll find it out what it is.</i>

26
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,693
[Jalil] <i>You're smart, Agent Angeles.</i>

27
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:10,653
<i>But before you even</i>
<i>get the chance to find out,</i>

28
00:01:10,737 --> 00:01:11,654
<i>my mission will long be completed.</i>

29
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:13,448
<i>You'll never see me again.</i>

30
00:01:15,283 --> 00:01:21,998
[mysterious theme music playing]

31
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:34,761
- [morose music playing]
- [Marcus sighs]

32
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:37,305
[Usman] Brother.

33
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:40,433
Do you really believe
that Datu Rahman is safe now?

34
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:42,936
It's all in Sir Mustapha's hands now.

35
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:45,730
He won't tell me anything.

36
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:47,440
Surely he won't…

37
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:50,860
surrender to Mustapha
if he wasn't ready to tell the truth.

38
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:53,446
[breathes heavily]

39
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:54,989
But you know, brother,

40
00:01:56,658 --> 00:01:58,827
as long as those
bastard protectors of the syndicate

41
00:01:58,910 --> 00:02:02,413
are roaming freely here inside NLEA,

42
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:04,958
no one is truly safe.

43
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:06,793
You're right.

44
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:10,213
That's why we should
hurry up and capture them.

45
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,341
Brother.

46
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:18,304
I discovered one more thing
while I was on the island.

47
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:20,306
What is it, brother?

48
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:23,560
Harold is alive.

49
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:26,938
He's alive. He's on the island.

50
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:29,232
There's a family looking after him,

51
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:31,109
but he can't remember anything for now.

52
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,736
The PTSD really hit him hard.

53
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:39,242
[sighs] Brother, keep this between us.

54
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:42,370
His life will be put in danger.

55
00:02:42,453 --> 00:02:44,664
Harold's condition is still unstable.

56
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:48,251
They'll mercilessly kill him, no doubt.

57
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:50,336
Yes, brother.

58
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,338
Your secret is safe with me.

59
00:02:52,422 --> 00:02:53,631
Don't worry.

60
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,675
It'll all be over soon.

61
00:02:56,384 --> 00:02:58,177
There's someone
in the upper ranks on our side.

62
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:00,138
Mustapha.

63
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:02,181
[exhales sharply]

64
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:05,059
How can you be certain
that he's really on our side?

65
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:09,272
Why?

66
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:14,485
Do you think… he's suspicious?

67
00:03:16,195 --> 00:03:17,030
[breathes heavily]

68
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:19,282
For now… [sighs]

69
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:22,952
I have no reason to doubt him.

70
00:03:24,412 --> 00:03:26,122
But it's hard, brother.

71
00:03:27,415 --> 00:03:29,083
You can't trust anyone
so easily these days.

72
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:32,337
Apart from Azuelo,

73
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,757
you're the only one I fully trust.

74
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,640
[Marcus sighs]

75
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:50,063
[unsettling music playing]

76
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:52,732
[Marcus groans]

77
00:03:58,029 --> 00:04:00,156
Before, I only had to spy on Marcus,

78
00:04:00,698 --> 00:04:02,951
but now even Espina's up to something.

79
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:04,869
He's scheming something.

80
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:06,829
[in English] I know he's up to no good.

81
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,206
[in English] I just know it.

82
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:13,044
That bastard's really good, huh?

83
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:17,674
If he was really able to capture
and make Datu Rahman surrender,

84
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:20,385
do you think…

85
00:04:21,177 --> 00:04:23,846
he knows where Jalil Abubakar is hiding?

86
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:26,391
- [Felix] Huh?
- Jalil Abubakar?

87
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:28,476
What do I care about Jalil Abubakar?

88
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:30,728
Aren't we talking about Espina right now?

89
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:32,855
Espina is the thorn in my side right now.

90
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:34,983
Chill out, madam.

91
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:38,736
Well, they're family, aren't they?

92
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,406
They're probably hiding in the same place.

93
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:43,491
And…

94
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:46,869
I just want to get my revenge.

95
00:04:47,578 --> 00:04:49,539
Is that so bad? Huh?

96
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:51,958
[unsettling music playing]

97
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:03,720
I can't look at myself in the mirror…

98
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,724
without seeing this.

99
00:05:10,893 --> 00:05:13,730
- [bangs]
- This goddamn scar!

100
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:14,647
‪[music intensifies]

101
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:18,109
Because of him!

102
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:19,402
[breathes heavily]

103
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:20,820
You understand?

104
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:25,908
Can you not undress in front of me?

105
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:30,913
All of my scars are from my father.

106
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:34,125
Except this one.

107
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,043
‪[music subdues]

108
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,880
And this is the biggest one, Lara.

109
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:47,138
That's why I won't let him
get away with it.

110
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:52,101
I'll make him pay for it, Lara.

111
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:53,019
‪[music intensifies]

112
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:00,109
Felix, are you opening up to me?

113
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:04,906
Well, don't. 'Cause I don't give a damn.

114
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:12,163
[music intensifies, concludes]

115
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:15,083
[engines humming]

116
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:16,626
[car horn honking]

117
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:23,674
[indistinct chatter]

118
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,135
[In Arabic] Peace be upon you!

119
00:06:27,178 --> 00:06:29,972
[In Tausug] Ma'am, how much for this?

120
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:33,017
Son! [giggles]

121
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:36,521
It's so nice to see you, Usman!

122
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:37,855
I've missed you so much!

123
00:06:38,439 --> 00:06:39,774
Well…

124
00:06:39,857 --> 00:06:42,610
I did tell you to come live with me,

125
00:06:42,693 --> 00:06:44,487
so you wouldn't be alone at home!

126
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,697
How many times do I have to tell you?

127
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:48,908
I can't, because…

128
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:51,619
I can't… I can't just leave our house.

129
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:54,205
Your father worked hard for it.
We should treasure it.

130
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:55,456
‪[gentle music playing]

131
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,333
Hold on.

132
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:00,378
What brings you here?
Is there something wrong?

133
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:02,630
Come on, Ma.

134
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:05,633
You think I only visit
when something's wrong?

135
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:07,969
[laughing] Oh, son.

136
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:09,804
I know you like the back of my hand.

137
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:13,766
I know you're busy
with work, with your duty.

138
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,017
But…

139
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:18,604
I also know that you visit me
when you're troubled.

140
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:20,022
What is it?

141
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,149
Hmm?

142
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:23,568
[pensive music playing]

143
00:07:23,651 --> 00:07:24,652
Well, Ma…

144
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:26,737
[inhales sharply]

145
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:31,993
I'm not really sure if…
I made the right decision.

146
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:35,079
What decision?

147
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:39,208
Ma…

148
00:07:40,084 --> 00:07:42,003
I lied to my friend

149
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:44,380
in order to protect another person.

150
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:48,468
But it's only right
to protect that person.

151
00:07:49,469 --> 00:07:50,678
But Ma…

152
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,681
I don't think I can lie to my friend

153
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:55,933
because he trusts me a lot.

154
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,187
I feel like I'm betraying him.

155
00:08:00,813 --> 00:08:03,149
Ah… You know, son,

156
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:07,153
sometimes it's inevitable
to end up in such situations.

157
00:08:07,236 --> 00:08:11,115
However, it doesn't mean
that you're no longer a good friend.

158
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:15,870
Due to our commitment
and dedication for our job,

159
00:08:15,953 --> 00:08:18,581
you're just doing what you have to do.

160
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:26,589
Well, was the lie you made
a part of your duty?

161
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:28,633
[suspenseful sting]

162
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:32,762
You need to help Allan Espina.

163
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:35,264
Help Jalil on his mission.

164
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:39,060
Can I count on you, brother?

165
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:40,228
[suspenseful sting]

166
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:41,312
Yes, Ma.

167
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:44,273
It's a huge help

168
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:47,777
in resolving this big case
we're currently handling.

169
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:51,864
Then, you have your answer.

170
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:57,036
Since you're doing it
for the sake of your duty,

171
00:08:57,912 --> 00:09:00,039
your friend has to understand that,

172
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:02,291
and the day will come when he will.

173
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:09,215
[sullen music playing]

174
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:16,264
- Alright then. Take care.
- [Usman] I will.

175
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:18,224
Take good care.

176
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:23,271
‪[music concludes]

177
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,733
Watch your step. [chuckles]

178
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:29,485
They're already inside.

179
00:09:32,863 --> 00:09:34,240
[pensive music playing]

180
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:36,492
[Jean] Come in.

181
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:38,828
Welcome, Sir Marcus.

182
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:40,371
[Marcus] Thank you, Jean.

183
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,416
Good evening, Sir Marcus.

184
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:44,875
Good evening, everyone.

185
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:46,252
[door clicks shut]

186
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:53,968
[morose music playing]

187
00:09:55,553 --> 00:09:56,971
Good evening, ma'am.

188
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:03,561
[morose music continues]

189
00:10:04,312 --> 00:10:08,608
Harold's grandmother,
Lilian, can't make it.

190
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:11,986
She's not well enough to travel.

191
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,948
That's fine. I'll visit her myself.

192
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,117
Sir Marcus.

193
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,702
I need to know.

194
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:22,622
Are the rumors true?

195
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:27,084
Someone from the NLEA
is behind all of this?

196
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:31,839
Did they kill Patrick?

197
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,969
Is that why the investigation
is still ongoing?

198
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:40,181
Datu Rahman is telling the truth.

199
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:44,143
I believe in him.

200
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:45,978
He is innocent.

201
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:48,898
Someone else is the mastermind.

202
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:50,816
[Karen] Are you saying

203
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:55,613
that the very institution
Russel served wholeheartedly…

204
00:10:55,696 --> 00:10:59,533
- [Karen sobs]
- Is the one who killed him?

205
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:04,664
There are rogue elements within the NLEA.

206
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:09,126
And I am hunting them down.

207
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:15,216
I will make them pay
for what happened to my team,

208
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:16,801
to your loved ones.

209
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:21,889
They were like brothers to me.

210
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:23,599
[Jean sobs]

211
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:25,559
They were family.

212
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:30,189
I refuse to let
their deaths go unpunished.

213
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:32,900
I swear on my life.

214
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:35,403
I will give them justice.

215
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:40,825
[dramatic sting]

216
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:44,036
But for now,

217
00:11:45,704 --> 00:11:48,124
I want to apologize to you.

218
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:53,754
I'm sorry I didn't do enough
to protect them.

219
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:58,384
[soft sobbing]

220
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:04,306
[inhales deeply, sighs]

221
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,644
You did nothing wrong, Sir Marcus.

222
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,397
Don't blame yourself.

223
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,275
[sniffles] Every night…

224
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:19,113
we pray that…

225
00:12:19,196 --> 00:12:20,239
[sobs]

226
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:23,868
…justice will be served for their deaths.

227
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:26,454
And I know you want the same thing.

228
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:29,457
[sniffles] We trust you.

229
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:35,296
We believe you will keep your promise.

230
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:38,841
[man sobs]

231
00:12:38,924 --> 00:12:40,926
[Jean sobs softly]

232
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:47,850
[stirring music playing]

233
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:52,980
[engine humming]

234
00:12:53,063 --> 00:12:57,485
[intriguing music playing]

235
00:12:57,568 --> 00:12:58,736
[door clicks open]

236
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,574
- What've you got?
- [sighs]

237
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:07,620
Sir, that's where
Datu Rahman was picked up

238
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,538
by the cop wearing glasses earlier.

239
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:14,418
[dramatic sting]

240
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:17,171
I'm sure of it. I saw them.

241
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:24,011
[dramatic sting]

242
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:28,557
Jamilah, I called to tell you

243
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:30,935
that I'll be gone for a while.

244
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:35,189
Why, Jalil? Where are you going?

245
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:37,942
I'm going back to the island.

246
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:40,945
Wait. I'll go along.

247
00:13:41,028 --> 00:13:42,488
[Jalil] <i>Jamilah, no.</i>

248
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:46,784
Father wants me to check on our community.

249
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:49,662
I'll move faster by myself.

250
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:53,165
<i>Besides, we can't be seen together.</i>

251
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:55,417
If Father will need anything,

252
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:58,170
one of us has to be here to help him.

253
00:13:58,254 --> 00:13:59,255
Okay?

254
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:03,592
Okay, Jalil. Be careful.

255
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,515
[knocking on door]

256
00:14:09,598 --> 00:14:16,397
[tense music playing]

257
00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:19,692
Uncle Omar?

258
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:21,694
[knocking continues]

259
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:24,947
[music intensifies]

260
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:26,740
Aunt Norhana?

261
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:30,786
[knocking intensifies]

262
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:37,501
[tense music continues]

263
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,339
[tense music playing]

264
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:43,966
‪[dramatic sting]

265
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:51,724
‪[dramatic stinging]

266
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:54,351
[dramatic sting]

267
00:14:57,479 --> 00:14:58,522
‪[music subdues]

268
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:00,482
[pensive music playing]

269
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:01,817
[Jamilah] Doctor!

270
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:04,111
What are you doing here?

271
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:08,782
Sorry, Jamilah. I was
just worried about you.

272
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,784
I came by to check on you.

273
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:14,872
I saw on the news
that your father has surrendered.

274
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:19,960
Uh…

275
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,129
Yes, Doc.

276
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:23,339
[thuds]

277
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:24,757
Come in.

278
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:30,262
[pensive music playing]

279
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:34,391
[music turns unsettling]

280
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:37,978
[pensive music playing]

281
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,074
[pensive music playing]

282
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:53,369
- [pensive music continues]
- [car door closes]

283
00:15:53,452 --> 00:15:54,370
The deliveries are ready, ma'am.

284
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:55,829
[in English] Good.

285
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:58,290
Make sure they are properly distributed.

286
00:15:58,791 --> 00:15:59,959
[in English] No delays.

287
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:01,627
The General is in a hurry.

288
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:03,128
- [in English] Copy, ma'am.
- Mm.

289
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:04,171
You can count on us.

290
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:05,923
[in English] Okay.

291
00:16:11,428 --> 00:16:15,557
[grim music playing]

292
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,184
[engine starts]

293
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,147
Hit the road!

294
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:23,482
Move!

295
00:16:27,152 --> 00:16:34,076
[suspenseful music playing]

296
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:38,706
[tires screech]

297
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:43,711
[tires screech]

298
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:50,759
[tires screeching]

299
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:52,469
‪[tires screech]

300
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:12,865
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [door clicks shuts]

301
00:17:27,671 --> 00:17:31,717
- [door clicks open, shuts]
- [suspenseful music continues]

302
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,469
[engine starts]

303
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,108
‪[dramatic sting]

304
00:17:49,693 --> 00:17:55,783
[suspenseful music continues]

305
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:56,867
Mister Omar!

306
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:59,495
- Mister Omar!
- [rapid knocking]

307
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:01,413
- Who's there?
- [Rashid] Mister Omar! Miss Norhana!

308
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:02,372
It's Rashid!

309
00:18:02,956 --> 00:18:04,249
Rashid!

310
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:06,001
- Mister Omar, turn your TV on.
- Hmm?

311
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:07,419
- Huh?
- What's going on?

312
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:10,214
- Put <i>MMK</i> on.
- Omar.

313
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,510
[TV remote clicks]

314
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,554
[curious music playing]

315
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:22,226
I'm on my way to Damai Island,
once a happy island,

316
00:18:22,309 --> 00:18:28,816
now wrapped in sorrow,
and an ocean bathed in blood.

317
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:32,778
[Maya, in English] <i>Living here</i>
<i>used to be peaceful.</i>

318
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:37,116
<i>Until one night, everything changed.</i>

319
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:39,701
[in English] <i>And one</i>
<i>of the most tragic massacres</i>

320
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:41,995
<i>in our country's recent history</i>

321
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:44,289
<i>happened right there.</i>

322
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:45,958
M-Marcus?

323
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:53,340
[unsettling music playing]

324
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:57,094
[Maya] I've talked to some people

325
00:18:57,177 --> 00:18:59,972
who've been to Damai Island.

326
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:01,849
[Maya] <i>And they all said the same thing.</i>

327
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:06,687
<i>This island was almost like paradise.</i>

328
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:10,816
[unsettling music continues]

329
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:15,654
<i>But what we're seeing now</i>
<i>is far from what we expected.</i>

330
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:18,407
[gulps]

331
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:21,243
[unsettling music continues]

332
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:24,204
[Maya] <i>This island</i>
<i>used to be full of life.</i>

333
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:27,416
But now, it's turned into a graveyard,

334
00:19:27,499 --> 00:19:30,043
with so many buried around.

335
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:36,633
[Maya, in English] <i>The quiet</i>
<i>turned into deafening silence.</i>

336
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:41,847
[unsettling music continues]

337
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,657
[unsettling music continues]

338
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:03,952
We cover them with white cloth.

339
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:08,290
It's called <i>kafan</i> in Arabic,
which means "shroud".

340
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:12,753
It symbolizes humility and simplicity,

341
00:20:12,836 --> 00:20:17,090
and also modesty,
because everyone is equal.

342
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:20,135
No matter who you were
when you were alive,

343
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:24,431
we all end up
wrapped in the same white cloth

344
00:20:24,514 --> 00:20:26,016
when we die in Islam.

345
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:29,603
We bury them as soon as possible.

346
00:20:29,686 --> 00:20:34,024
Uh… Within 24 hours,
or even earlier, if possible.

347
00:20:34,107 --> 00:20:36,693
One reason for this is,

348
00:20:36,777 --> 00:20:40,113
if a person is destined for paradise,

349
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:44,743
our belief in Islam
is that even in the grave,

350
00:20:44,826 --> 00:20:47,996
they are shown peace
and comfort as a reward

351
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:51,416
for their sacrifices
while they were alive in this world.

352
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,586
That is why we bury them immediately.

353
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:55,837
Thank you very much, Imam.

354
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:57,047
Thank you as well.

355
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:59,508
[in English] I am now
with some of the survivors

356
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:01,885
of the massacre
that happened just recently.

357
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:05,097
[Maya] <i>The pain is still fresh</i>
<i>in their hearts and minds.</i>

358
00:21:05,847 --> 00:21:07,557
<i>Just like Fatima Kareem.</i>

359
00:21:08,558 --> 00:21:10,435
[In Tausug] <i>We were so happy that night.</i>

360
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,771
<i>We were having a meal together.</i>

361
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:15,691
[Fatima] The elders were talking,

362
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:20,821
and the children were playing. [sniffles]

363
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:25,117
Then… suddenly, gunshots rang out.

364
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,743
[gunshot]

365
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:28,620
[overlapping dialogue]

366
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:32,749
[Fatima] <i>Then after that,</i>

367
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,626
<i>bullets were raining down on us.</i>

368
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:39,381
- [rapid gunfire]
- <i>Then I saw my child…</i>

369
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:41,925
<i>Ariza.</i>

370
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:47,431
<i>She was trembling in fear,</i>

371
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:50,642
<i>and she couldn't run anymore.</i>

372
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:52,602
[sobbing]

373
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:55,689
<i>I wanted to save my child,</i>

374
00:21:56,898 --> 00:22:00,444
<i>but before I could even reach her,</i>

375
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:04,031
<i>she was riddled with bullets.</i> [sobbing]

376
00:22:04,114 --> 00:22:09,453
[Fatima sobbing vehemently]

377
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:18,503
[Maryam sobbing] <i>My husband</i>
<i>had a good catch that day.</i>

378
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:22,299
<i>So we were planning to go to the city</i>

379
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:28,013
<i>to buy new shoes for Harun.</i>

380
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:29,806
[sobbing]

381
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:33,643
<i>That was what he wished for</i>

382
00:22:34,895 --> 00:22:37,606
<i>on his birthday.</i>

383
00:22:38,857 --> 00:22:42,110
[unsettling music continues]

384
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:44,905
They're not just my neighbors.

385
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:48,241
[sobbing] They're my friends.

386
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:52,412
We've been together since childhood.

387
00:22:55,415 --> 00:22:59,294
When Datu Rahman
and his son, Jalil, disappeared,

388
00:23:00,003 --> 00:23:02,130
we lost our protectors.

389
00:23:02,214 --> 00:23:07,344
[unsettling music continues]

390
00:23:07,427 --> 00:23:09,596
<i>Illegal firearms have been spreading</i>

391
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:12,516
<i>in areas near our island.</i>

392
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:14,184
<i>They're ending up</i>
<i>in the hands of criminals.</i>

393
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:16,812
[unsettling music continues]

394
00:23:17,437 --> 00:23:18,939
<i>If they attack us here,</i>

395
00:23:19,022 --> 00:23:20,732
<i>there'll be no one left to defend us.</i>

396
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:24,778
<i>And just like his father,</i>

397
00:23:25,278 --> 00:23:28,365
<i>they're now accusing Jalil</i>
<i>of being a criminal too.</i>

398
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:31,868
[music intensifying]

399
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:47,759
[Maya] <i>According to Datu Rahman Abubakar,</i>

400
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:50,846
<i>those behind the massacre</i>
<i>are from the NLEA.</i>

401
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:53,682
<i>Now that he has surrendered</i>
<i>and is in government custody,</i>

402
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:58,145
<i>are we even close to finding out</i>
<i>who really did this to Damai Island?</i>

403
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:03,900
It's easy to say the word massacre.

404
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:06,361
[in English] We all know what it means.

405
00:24:06,444 --> 00:24:11,908
But until we see the faces
of those who lived through it,

406
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:16,413
we will never fully understand
the gravity, the sorrow,

407
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:19,666
and the injustice that this word entails.

408
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:25,463
[Maya] <i>And the victims,</i>
<i>along with their families,</i>

409
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:26,965
<i>only have one wish…</i>

410
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:28,884
<i>justice.</i>

411
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:35,265
[morose music playing]

412
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:46,109
[morose music playing]

413
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:09,466
[dramatic stinging]

414
00:25:17,098 --> 00:25:18,141
I'm begging you!

415
00:25:18,225 --> 00:25:21,311
Have respect for our mourning
and leave now!

416
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:26,274
[morose music continues]

417
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:40,705
[dramatic music playing]

418
00:26:03,019 --> 00:26:05,730
[Felix] <i>What is Marcus's mother</i>
<i>doing here?</i>

419
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:08,400
<i>Why does she seem</i>
<i>so important in this place?</i>

420
00:26:08,483 --> 00:26:10,402
I invited Allan over.

421
00:26:10,485 --> 00:26:11,653
Be careful, son.

422
00:26:11,736 --> 00:26:13,071
You might even start calling him your son.

423
00:26:14,114 --> 00:26:17,534
People are saying
we're protecting the culprit

424
00:26:17,617 --> 00:26:20,120
because he's one of us!
They've lost trust in us!

425
00:26:20,203 --> 00:26:22,080
General Villanueva is convinced

426
00:26:22,163 --> 00:26:23,540
by what Datu Rahman is saying!

427
00:26:23,623 --> 00:26:27,127
The accusations against Datu Rahman
aren't true.

428
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:29,170
What's going on?
Do you know something I don't?

429
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:30,964
[Lara] <i>Because I want to understand.</i>

430
00:26:31,047 --> 00:26:35,218
[Manuel] <i>Give them what they need.</i>

431
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:36,428
[Felix] <i>Go to Damai Island.</i>

432
00:26:36,511 --> 00:26:39,931
- Eliminate everyone left there.
- Yes, boss.

433
00:26:40,015 --> 00:26:43,727
[Felix] <i>Taste my revenge, Jalil Abubakar.</i>
